<reference id="reference_tbl_h45_ls">
  <title><cmdname>server-list</cmdname></title>
  <shortdesc>Lists servers in a cluster.</shortdesc>
  <refbody>
    <section><title>Syntax</title>
      <p>The basic syntax is:</p>
      <codeblock>couchbase-cli server-list -c [localhost]:8091 -u Administrator -p password    </codeblock>
    </section>  <section><title>Description</title>
      <p> Use this command to list the servers in a cluster.</p>   
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Options</title>
      <p>The following are the command options:</p>
      <table><title>server-list options</title>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1*"/>
          <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.08*"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Parameter</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry><codeph>--group-name=GROUPNAME</codeph></entry>
              <entry>Displays all server in a server group (Enterprise Edition only)</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
      
    </section> 
    
    <section>
      <title>Examples</title>
      
      
      <p>Lists the servers:</p>
      <codeblock>couchbase-cli server-list -c 192.168.0.1:8091 -u Administrator -p password</codeblock>
    </section>
   
  </refbody>
